steps.section: Preparation of bacterial cell lysate for SDS-PAGE
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"fp6ql","text":"Grow the cells overnight, to an OD600 above 1. If IPTG induction needed, at it around OD600 0.2-0.3 (keep IPTG stock solution at -20 freezer).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":34,"length":3},{"style":"sub","offset":88,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of bacterial cell lysate for SDS-PAGE
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"65dc","text":"Take one 1 ml of OD600 = 1 from each sample. Correct the sample volume to obtain an equivalent size pellet. For us, as quantified using NanoCym950 nanoparticles (equivalent to the size of E. coli), 1 OD600 equals to 10^8 nanoparticles per mL. We estimate each well on SDS-PAGE contains proteins from 2*10^6 bacteria.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":19,"length":3},{"style":"italic","offset":188,"length":7}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of bacterial cell lysate for SDS-PAGE
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"3aecs","text":"Spin down the bacterial cells for 1 min at 13,000 rpm in a microfuge.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of bacterial cell lysate for SDS-PAGE
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"91emu","text":"Aspirate any trace of supernatant with a vacuum line avoiding touching the pellet, but removing all liquid. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Preparation of bacterial cell lysate for SDS-PAGE
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"d71vf","text":"To each cell pellet, add 250 µL of distilled water, resuspend the pellet. Add 250 µL 2x SDS sample buffer (see below). Heat with a 95 degree heating block for 10 minutes. Store the samples at -20 degree freezer until SDS-PAGE.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9heds","text":"2x SDS sample buffer, works for Tris-Cl or MOPS based gels","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fkglt","text":"Glycerol 20 ml","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"4bs5f","text":"SDS 4 g","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6d2m","text":"0.5 M Tris-HCl pH 6.8 stock solution 25 ml","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"ahuog","text":"Bromo Phenol Blue 1 mg; dissolve and volume to 95 ml","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8bh1r","text":"add 5% β-Mercaptoethanol before usage","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
